By default, the URL path consists of the categories and the item name.
plentymarkets automatically assigns the path when the item is created. The path is displayed as part of the URL when the item is viewed in the plentyShop.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Meta description</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div class="content"><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter a meta description for the item (max. 350 characters).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><em>Note</em></strong>: The meta description makes it easier for search engines to find the item.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Meta keywords</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div class="content"><div class="paragraph">
<p>Enter keywords for the item (max. 1000 characters).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong><em>Note</em></strong>: The meta keywords make it easier for search engines to find the item.</p>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><p class="tableblock"><strong>Item template</strong></p></td>
<td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"><div class="content"><div class="paragraph">
<p>Not recommended. It’s technically possible to select a <a href="/en/item/online-store/callisto-templates">template</a> to alter the design of the detail view of an item.
However, we don’t recommend doing so for two reasons:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Item templates overwrite your “normal” product pages and are therefore not particularly useful in real life situations.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>This procedure is more complicated than <a href="https://vimeo.com/360260315">designing product pages with ShopBuilder</a> (see German video starting from minute 12:17).</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div></div></td>
</tr>
